'''Dick Ukeiwé''' (13 December 1928 – 3 September 2013) was a [[New Caledonia]]n politician.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/members/archive/alphaOrder/view.do;jsessionid=961CF48C08348DF91603000877319C42.node1?language=FR&id=1017 |title=Vos députés : Dick UKEIWÉ |publisher=Europarl.europa.eu |date= |accessdate=2013-09-05}}</ref> Born in [[Lifou]], [[France]], he represented the island in the [[Senate (France)|French Senate]] from 1983 until 1992, and was a member of the [[Rally for the Republic]].<ref>{{cite web|author=S&eacute;nat fran&ccedil;ais |url=http://www.senat.fr/senateur/ukeiwe_dick59250h.html |title=Anciens sénateurs Vème République : UKEIWE Dick |publisher=Senat.fr |date= |accessdate=2013-09-05}}</ref><ref name=Death>{{cite web |url=http://m.tahiti-infos.com/Deces-de-Dick-Ukeiwe-ancien-dirigeant-kanak-pro-francais_a82589.html |title=Décès de Dick Ukeiwé, ancien dirigeant kanak pro-français |language=French |publisher=M.tahiti-infos.com |date= |accessdate=2013-09-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610214648/http://m.tahiti-infos.com/Deces-de-Dick-Ukeiwe-ancien-dirigeant-kanak-pro-francais_a82589.html |archivedate=2015-06-10 |df= }}</ref> His son, [[Bernard Ukeiwé]] (1953–2008), was also a New Caledonian politician. Dick died, aged 84, on 3 September 2013 in [[Dumbéa]]. He is survived by four children.<ref name=Death/>

