{{Infobox person | name = Fred Tolit | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Uganda]] | death_date = | death_place = | education = |occupation = [[Military officer|Military Officer]] | years_active = 1995 - present | nationality = [[Uganda]]n | citizenship = [[Uganda]] | residence = [[Kampala]], [[Uganda]] | known_for = [[Military|Military Matters]] | networth = | home_town = [[Kampala]] | title = }}
[[Brigadier]] '''Fred Tolit''', is a [[military officer]]. He currently serves as ''[[Uganda]]'s Defense Attaché'' to the headquarters of the [[African Union]] in [[Addis Ababa]], [[Ethiopia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/news/648445-brig-tolit-appointed-defence-envoy-to-au.html|title=Brigadier Tolit Appointed Defence Envoy to AU|publisher=[[New Vision]]|date=16 October 2013| last=Kwesiga|first=Pascal|accessdate=11 June 2014}}</ref> Prior to that, he served as the '''Chairman of the UPDF General Court Martial''', one of the highest military courts in the [[Uganda People's Defence Force]] (UPDF). He was replaced by [[Moses Ddiba Ssentongo|Brigadier Moses Ddiba Ssentongo]], the current Chairman, in June 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/news/644406-brig-ssentongo-appointed-new-army-court-boss.html|title=Brigadier Ssentongo Appointed New Army Court Boss|publisher=[[New Vision]]| date=27 June 2013|first=Pascal|last=Kwesiga|accessdate=11 June 2014}}</ref>
==Background== He was born in [[Northern Region, Uganda|Northern Uganda]].
==Military career== His military career includes service in the flowing capacities: <ref>{{cite web|title=Brigadier Tolit Appointed Defence Envoy to AU| url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/mobile/Detail.aspx?NewsID=648445&CatID=1|first=Pascal|last=Kwesiga|date=16 October 2013|accessdate=11 June 2014|publisher=[[New Vision|New Vision Mobile]]}}</ref> * As Director of Military Intelligence, from 1993 until 1998.<ref>{{cite web|date=19 June 2013|accessdate=11 June 2014| url=http://www.observer.ug/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=25943:museveni-picks-saleh-to-lead-retirement-team|title=Museveni Picks Saleh to Lead Retirement Team|first=Reporter|last=Our|publisher=[[The Observer (Uganda)]]}}</ref> * As Chief of Operations and Training in UPDF in 1998. * As Commander of the 2nd Infantry Division, between 2000 and 2001. * As the Assistant Army Chief of Staff, at the level of [[Colonel]], between 2001 and 2003. * As Defense Liaison Officer at the [[East African Community]], headquarters in [[Arusha]], [[Tanzania]], between 2005 and 2009. * As Defence Attaché to Uganda's permanent mission to the [[United Nations]] headquarters in [[New York City|New York]]. * As Chairman of the General Court Martial of the UPDF, at the rank of [[Brigadier]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=11 June 2014|url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/news/634134-brig-tolit-sworn-in-as-new-court-martial-chairman.html|title=Brigadier Tolit Sworn In As New Court Martial Chairman|publisher=[[New Vision]]|date=15 August 2012|first=Jeff Andrew|last=Lule}}</ref> * As Uganda's Defence Attaché at the African Union headquarters in Addis Ababa, starting in 2013.
